Thorax. Generally brownish yellow to brown. Pronotum dark brown. Prescutum brownish yellow with three broad dark brown stripes. Scutum, scutellum and mediotergite dark brown (Fig. 9d). Pleuron (Fig. 9
a-b
) dark brown with ventral region paler. Hairs on thorax dark brown. Coxa and trochanters pale brownish yellow; remainder of legs dark brown. Hairs on legs brownish black. Wing (Fig. 9e) tinged pale grey; veins pale brown. Venation: Sc1 ending a short distance beyond origin of Rs, Sc2 a slightly greater distance before origin of Rs; R2+3 ending before end of basal section of R4+5; basal section of CuA1 before fork of M; A1 curved suddenly at middle, basal half straight. Haltere length 0.7-0.8 mm, pale brownish yellow.

Abdomen (Fig. 9
a-b
). Dark brown, only hypopygium paler. Hairs on abdomen dark brown.
